er studio arrangement returns, with the large Serutan Plus display on the left and the presenter on the right. He now holds the bottle near his chest, keeping it visible while addressing the viewer. He stands upright in his suit, occasionally lifting a finger as if making a key point, then bringing both hands around the bottle in a presenting gesture. The oversized display remains unchanged: “NEW LAXATIVE ADVANCE,” “For Fast Relief of Irregularity,” “NEW SERUTAN PLUS,” the capsule graphic, the bottle illustration, and the smaller line about soothing medication are all visible.\n\nThe commercial ends on a clean product graphic rather than the presenter. On the left are two Serutan Plus packages: a rectangular carton and a glass bottle or jar, both labeled “SERUTAN PLUS.” Across the top, large raised-looking letters read “NEW LAXATIVE ADVANCE.” To the right, a framed rectangular panel first reads “FAST RELIEF.” Along the bottom, a bold dark banner carries the product name “SERUTAN PLUS” in large white letters. The right-hand panel then changes from “FAST RELIEF” to “GENTLE RELIEF,” while the carton, bottle, top headline, and bottom Serutan Plus banner remain fixed in place.",
